# Network Troubleshooting:
# Common Tools: Familiarize yourself with tools such as ping, traceroute, netstat, and Wireshark
# Troubleshooting Methodologies: Learn systematic approaches to diagnosing and resolving network issues

Network Protocols:
TCP/UDP: Understand the differences between TCP (reliable, connection-oriented) and UDP (fast, connectionless) protocols
DNS: Learn how the Domain Name System translates domain names into IP addresses

Bandwidth: Understand how data transmission rates are measured and managed
Quality of Service (QoS): Learn how QoS policies prioritize certain types of network traffic to ensure performance
